<paragraph blockId="5.[827,1443,1270,1599]" pageId="5" pageNumber="700">
<emphasis box="[827,956,1271,1292]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="700">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Large, oval organisms (&gt; 
<quantity box="[1291,1375,1271,1292]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="700" unit="mm" value="30.0">30 mm</quantity>
total length). Valves flattened to elevated and carinate, with pectinated insertions. Tegmental structure variable, subtegmentum poorly to highly developed. Girdle scales variable in shape and size, smooth or with striations, pustules or granules. Denticle cap of major lateral tooth of radula variable, blunt or somewhat elongate or round; angle of denticle cap greater than 90° from axis of the tooth itself; distal edge of centrolateral tooth perpendicular to longitudinal axis of animal.
</paragraph>
